HEADWORD: crumpet
<hw>crump"et</hw> <pr>(kr⟦ucr⟧mp"⟦ecr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob.
from W. <ets>crempog</ets>, <ets>crammwgth</ets>, a pancake or
fritter.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A kind of large, thin, unsweetened
muffin or cake, light and spongy, and cooked on a griddle or spider, or
sometimes toasted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a sexually attractive woman.</def> <mark>[British
slang]</mark> <au>RHUD</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crumple</ent>⟦br⟧
